# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# <footer>
#
# === CONVENTIONAL COMMITS FORMAT ===
#
# Types (lowercase only):
#   feat:     New feature for the user
#   fix:      Bug fix for the user
#   docs:     Documentation only changes
#   test:     Adding/updating tests
#   chore:    Maintenance tasks
#   refactor: Code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
#   style:    Formatting, missing semicolons, etc.
#   perf:     Performance improvement
#   ci:       CI/CD configuration changes
#   build:    Build system or external dependencies
#   merge:    Merge commits
#   security: Security-related changes
#   revert:   Revert a previous commit
#
# Scope (optional):
#   Component or module being changed
#   Examples: (api), (lwc), (apex), (auth), (dashboard)
#
# Subject:
#   - Use imperative mood: "Add feature" not "Added feature"
#   - Don't capitalize first letter
#   - No period at the end
#   - Max 72 characters
#
# Body (optional):
#   - Explain what and why, not how
#   - Wrap at 72 characters
#
# Footer (optional):
#   - Reference issues: Fixes #123, Closes #456
#   - Breaking changes: BREAKING CHANGE: <description>
#
# === EXAMPLES ===
#
# feat: add user authentication flow
# fix(api): resolve timeout on large requests
# docs: update installation guide
# test(dashboard): add unit tests for score calculation
# chore: update dependencies
# refactor(apex): extract validation to separate method
# security: add CRUD checks to DML operations
